Pros:
Reliability:
Durable Storage: Metrics are temporarily stored in S3, ensuring data isnâ€™t lost if downstream systems (e.g., Lambda, vectordotdev) face outages.
Reprocessing Capability: Metrics in S3 can be reprocessed in case of downstream issues.
Scalability:
S3 acts as a buffer, ensuring that high loads are absorbed and downstream systems arenâ€™t overwhelmed.
Flexibility: The Lambda function can perform data transformation, enrichment, or filtering before posting metrics to vectordotdev.
